6:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"GMX uses oracle-based pricing with GLP/GM liquidity pools acting as counterparties, leading to funding rates that reflect pool imbalances rather than pure market sentiment. Paradex operates a traditional order book model with funding rates calculated from mark-to-index price differences. GMX's oracle dependency can create arbitrage opportunities when oracle prices lag spot markets, while Paradex's institutional-grade infrastructure aims for tighter spreads and more accurate funding rate discovery."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which exchange offers better funding rate opportunities?","answer":"Paradex's lower fees and order book model typically provide more accurate funding rates, while GMX's oracle-based system can create unique arbitrage opportunities when oracle prices diverge from market reality."},{"question":"How do liquidity mechanisms differ between GMX and Paradex?","answer":"GMX uses GLP/GM pools where LPs provide liquidity against all traders, while Paradex operates a traditional order book where traders provide liquidity to each other. This affects funding rate calculations and available liquidity depth."},{"question":"Which platform is better for institutional funding rate strategies?","answer":"Paradex targets institutional users with portfolio margin and Jump Trading expertise, while GMX serves retail with simpler mechanics. Institutions typically prefer Paradex's lower fees and familiar order book structure."},{"question":"What are the main risks when comparing these platforms?","answer":"GMX carries oracle dependency risk and higher fees but offers proven stability. Paradex presents early-stage platform risk and StarkNet complexity but provides institutional-grade infrastructure with lower costs."}]}]
